			<div id="season">
				<h3>Retreiving games by season</h3>
				<h4>Parameters</h4>
				<pre>?season={integer:season}</pre>
				<pre>?season={integer:season}&week={integer:week}</pre>
				<h4>Description</h4>
				<p>Queries with these paramters will return historical data for the season and week provided. Historical data is available from 1985 to 2014 via <a href="https://collegefootballapi.com">College Football API</a>.</p>
				<p><b>NOTE</b>: While the schema for games is the same as that for the latest data from ESPN, there is not as much metadata avilable for each game.
					This is mainly due to me not being able to successfully write asynchronus requests and retrieve that data.
					As a stopgap, I have included the URL to query for that data. If you know how to fix this issue, please submit a <a href="https://github.com/akeaswaran/cfb-scoreboard-api/pulls">pull request</a>.</p>
				<h4>Sample request</h4>
				<code>http://cfb-scoreboard-api.herokuapp.com/scoreboard?season=2014&week=10</code>
				<h4>Sample reponse</h4>
				<pre>
{
	"retrievedAt": "2016-01-09T03:40:17.596Z",
	"week": "10",
	"season": "2014",
	"cfbUrl": "https://collegefootballapi.com/api/1.0/season/2014/week/10",
	"games": [
	  {
	    "id": 103896,
